    <string name="settings_privacy_policy_title">Privacy policy</string>
    <string name="settings_privacy_policy_summary">Local-first diagnostics with optional Google sign-in.</string>
    <string name="settings_privacy_policy_body">DeviceDNA reads hardware and system diagnostics on your device to show CPU, memory, battery, storage, sensor, camera, app and network information. Sensitive identifiers are masked by default. Google sign-in is used only to identify your account through Firebase Authentication; DeviceDNA does not sell hardware diagnostics or upload them to a private server. Ads may be served by Google Mobile Ads and can contact Google services. Optional features that need network access, such as public IP lookup or Firebase authentication, may contact Google or the selected network endpoint and are clearly opt-in. You can sign out, disable public IP lookup, keep IMEI and serial values hidden, reduce background monitoring, and revoke Android permissions at any time in system settings.</string>

